# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# .gitignore — Tells Git which files to NEVER track
#
# WHY THIS FILE EXISTS:
#   Without .gitignore, `git add .` would commit build artifacts, IDE files,
#   secrets, and OS files. This creates:
#     - Repository bloat (hundreds of MB of compiled classes)
#     - Security leaks (credentials accidentally committed)
#     - Merge conflicts (IDE settings differ per developer)
#     - Broken CI (compiled code from wrong Java version checked in)
#
# RULE: Commit SOURCE files. Never commit GENERATED files.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# MAVEN BUILD OUTPUT
# Maven compiles Java → .class files in /target.
# The fat JAR is also in /target.
# These are GENERATED — rebuild from source anytime.
# Committing them causes: binary file conflicts, bloated diffs, wrong-version JARs.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
target/
!.mvn/wrapper/maven-wrapper.jar
!**/src/main/**/target/
!**/src/test/**/target/

# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# MAVEN WRAPPER
# maven-wrapper.properties tells Maven which version to use.
# The JAR is small and should be committed so the project is self-contained.
# (Exception to the .jar rule above — see the !.mvn/wrapper/ line)
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.mvn/

# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# IntelliJ IDEA IDE FILES
# .idea/ = project settings, run configurations, code style preferences
# *.iml = module definition files
# These are IDE-specific. VSCode users don't need .idea. Vim users don't need it.
# Committing IDE files causes constant merge conflicts between team members.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.idea/
*.iws
*.iml
*.ipr
out/

# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ECLIPSE IDE FILES
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.apt_generated
.classpath
.factorypath
.project
.settings
.springBeans
.sts4-cache

# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# VISUAL STUDIO CODE
# .vscode/settings.json stores workspace settings — may differ per developer.
# Exception: .vscode/extensions.json (recommended extensions) IS worth committing.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.vscode/

# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OPERATING SYSTEM FILES
# macOS creates .DS_Store in every directory for Finder metadata.
# Windows creates Thumbs.db for image thumbnails.
# These are NEVER relevant to the project.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo

# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ENVIRONMENT AND SECRETS — MOST CRITICAL SECTION
# .env files often contain:
#   DATABASE_URL=postgres://user:password@host:5432/db
#   AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=AKIA...
#   JWT_SECRET=supersecret
# NEVER commit these. If you do, rotate ALL credentials immediately.
# Secret scanning tools (GitHub, GitGuardian) alert on these patterns.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
*.env
application-local.properties
application-secret.properties
secrets.properties

# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# LOG FILES
# Log files grow indefinitely and contain sensitive runtime data.
# They are generated at runtime — never commit them.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.log
logs/

# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DOCKER
# .dockerignore handles this at the Docker layer.
# These are local Docker desktop files.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
docker-compose.override.yml

# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SPRING BOOT DEVTOOLS
# DevTools restart files — used for hot-reload in development only.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
spring-devtools.properties
